{
  "text": "The natural habitats of C. arabica and C. canephora are the humid, evergreen forests of Africa [CITATION_1] : the former is a high-altitude species (900-2000 m a.s.l.) of south-western Ethiopia and the surrounding regions; the latter is a predominately lowland plant (50-1500 m a.s.l.) found throughout much of tropical Africa, west of the Rift Valley [CITATION_2] . One aspect of paramount importance in dealing with the basic biology of H. hampei has been determining its alternative host plants in Africa, i.e. are there plants other than C. arabica and C. canephora that, in their natural habitat, are suitable for the reproduction and development of the insect?",
  "citation_candidates": [
